org.apache.spark.ml.feature

RegexTokenizer

class RegexTokenizer extends UnaryTransformer[String, Seq[String], RegexTokenizer]

:: AlphaComponent :: A regex based tokenizer that extracts tokens either by repeatedly matching the regex(default) or using it to split the text (set matching to false). Optional parameters also allow to fold the text to lowercase prior to it being tokenized and to filer tokens using a minimal length. It returns an array of strings that can be empty. The default parameters are regex = "\\p{L}+|[^\\p{L}\\s]+", matching = true, lowercase = false, minTokenLength = 1
